                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 11513/1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Bryan</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-02-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Bacon informs Mr. Bryan that the President has sent to the young King and to
                    the bereaved Queen Mother a personal message of sympathy, and directs him to
                    tender to the Portuguese Government through the usual channels the condolence
                    and sympathetic sorrow of the people of the United States. In the absence of Mr.
                    Root Mr. Bryan is requested to convey to the minister for foreign affairs
                    adequate expression of Mr. Bacon’s personal sentiments.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
